  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-05 18:09 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] OBI Filter Design \u2014 High-Conviction Trade Selector\n\n**Task:** Analyze April trade data to design a new OBI-based filter that cuts losing trades while preserving winners.\n\n**Finding:** Massive edge differential by Order Book Imbalance (OBI) in April data (27 trades):\n\n| OBI Bucket | Trades | Win Rate | Pattern |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| OBI < -0.5 (strong sell pressure) | 6 | **83%** | Our contrarian YES bets crush when book is stacked against us |\n| OBI [-0.2, +0.2] (neutral) | 7 | **86%** | Balanced books = clean signal, high conviction |\n| OBI [+0.2, +0.5) (mild buy pressure) | 4 | 75% | Still decent |\n| OBI \u2265 +0.5 (strong buy pressure) | 6 | **33%** | Disaster zone \u2014 book agrees with us but we still lose |\n\nKey insight: When OBI > +0.5 (strong buy-side pressure), our YES trades are only **33% WR**. These are the \"crowded trade\" \u2014 everyone's buying YES, the book is stacked bullish, and the market has already moved. Our contrarian edge evaporates.\n\nCombined filter simulation (|bias|\u226550 AND OBI<0.5):\n- **17 trades, 76% WR, cumulative pnl_pct = +8.19** (better than unfiltered +7.98)\n- Blocked 10 trades at **50% WR** \u2014 cutting coin flips\n\nV5A filter validation: PASS=71% WR (14 trades), BLOCK=25% WR (4 trades) \u2014 V5A is working perfectly, confirming bias threshold of 45+ matters.\n\n**My thinking:** The OBI signal reveals something elegant: our contrarian strategy works best when the order book DISAGREES with our direction or is neutral. When the book agrees with us (OBI > +0.5), we're not contrarian anymore \u2014 we're following the crowd into an already-priced-in move. The 33% WR at high positive OBI is catastrophic and consistent.\n\nThis is a V7 candidate filter. Conservative approach: soft-block OBI > 0.5 first (log but don't trade), collect 2 weeks of data, then hard-block if pattern holds.\n\n**Decision:** \n1. **NOT deploying yet** \u2014 it's Sunday, weekend filter is active, and we want Monday weekday data first\n2. Design V7 spec: `if obi > 0.5: skip trade (tag: OBI_CROWDED)` \n3. This would have saved 4 losses in April (worth ~$40-50 in avoided losses)\n4. Will draft V7 code and backtest against March data next P3 heartbeat\n5. Sample size still small (27 trades) \u2014 need 50+ before hard deployment\n\n**Current Status:**\n- PM balance: **$871.70** (weekend, no trades \u2014 V3.3 weekend filter active)\n- HL balance: **$37.39** (frozen, per recapitalization plan)\n- April WR: **66.7%** (18W/9L) \u2014 above breakeven but below 73% target\n- Both bots alive and running\n\n**V7 OBI Filter Draft Spec:**\n```\n# In should_trade(), after bias filters, before regime filter:\nobi_val = self._last_indicators.get('obi', 0) or 0\nif obi_val > 0.5:\n    return None, 0, f\"OBI_CROWDED (obi={obi_val:+.3f}, >0.5 = 33% WR)\"\n```\n\n**Next (P3):** \n- Backtest V7 OBI filter against ALL historical trades (not just April)\n- Draft V7 code change in trading_bot.py\n- Prep",
